<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>

<p>In the <a href="https://atom-morgan.github.io/properties-and-methods/" target="_blank">previous tutorial</a> we introduced properties and methods such as <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.length</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.charAt()</code> as well as the logical operators AND and OR. We finished by writing our first iterative code using the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">for</code> loop.</p>

<p>Up until this point we‚Äôve been calling functions (also referred to as methods) like <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">console.log()</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.charAt()</code>. In this tutorial we‚Äôre going to switch from <em>calling</em> functions to <em>writing</em> them as well.</p>

